Package agents

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Message
    A message object that is instantiated to send message back and forth between MetaAgents.
    MetaAgent
    Abstract MetaAgent class that implements a receiving and parsing behaviour for incoming message.
    Portal
    A Portal MetaAgent whose main purpose is to redirect incoming messages to its children.
    SystemAgent
    An abstract system-level agent that is used to discern a difference in heading for its child classes.
    SystemMessage
    A specialised message whose construction is restricted to the current program.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Flags
    A flaggable enumeration example for Java where the Message flags are specified using bit-shifted values and stored in the message via an integer.
    Protocol
    The message protocol for specialised implementations of the Meta-Agent system.
    SystemAction
    An action to be applied to a SystemMessage.
    Wildcard
    A Wildcard operator is used to easily distinguish unique recipients for Messages in the case where it is required.
